 :tx/rationale "EPISTEMOLOGICAL-CHAIN: The system has four layers forming the complete knowledge pipeline: Intent (observations, decisions — what the agent experiences), Specification (INVs, ADRs, NEGs — what's formally agreed), Implementation (code, traces — what's built), Behavior (test results, witnesses — what's verified). These recapitulate the epistemological chain from subjective to empirical: Intent=subjective, Spec=intersubjective, Impl=objective, Behavior=empirical. Three adjacent boundaries connect them: (1) Intent↔Spec (crystallization — observations become spec elements), (2) Spec↔Impl (implementation — spec elements get code+tests), (3) Impl↔Behavior (verification — code gets witnesses). The coherence state is fully characterized by the tightness of these three links. F(S)=1.0 means all four levels are aligned. The reconciliation taxonomy maps directly: Epistemic+Axiological divergence = Intent↔Spec boundary, Structural divergence = Spec↔Impl boundary, Behavioral divergence = Impl↔Behavior boundary. The other divergence types (logical, aleatory, temporal, procedural) are second-order — they operate within or across these primary boundaries. CRITICAL FINDING: braid observe lives at the Intent↔Spec boundary. Currently this boundary has ZERO per-transaction measurement. The 252 untested INVs gap and the crystallization backlog (32 observations) are both symptoms of unmeasured boundaries. TRACES TO: SEED.md §2 (divergence types), SEED.md §6 (reconciliation taxonomy), INV-BILATERAL-001 (bilateral convergence)."
